1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
MkvDrama.net

2
00:02:46,181 --> 00:02:47,349
Happy New Year, Jay.

3
00:02:49,059 --> 00:02:50,952
<i>Why did you even do that, Jay-jay?</i>

4
00:02:50,977 --> 00:02:52,187
My only wish is that...

5
00:02:52,246 --> 00:02:53,789
in the end, you'll still choose me.

6
00:02:53,814 --> 00:02:56,566
<i>You’re already engaged to Yuri, </i>
<i>time to forget about Keif-</i>

7
00:02:56,608 --> 00:02:57,482
Fuck!

8
00:02:57,507 --> 00:02:59,243
Profanity on the first day back?

9
00:02:59,891 --> 00:03:00,855
I'm jealous.

10
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,798
You agreed to be my fiancée.

11
00:03:02,823 --> 00:03:04,116
Falling in love is so hard.

12
00:03:04,116 --> 00:03:06,176
There are two guys chasing after you.

13
00:03:06,348 --> 00:03:07,516
Can I kiss you again?

14
00:03:08,704 --> 00:03:10,288
Why are you doing this to me, Jay?

15
00:03:10,288 --> 00:03:11,832
Tell me and I'll leave you alone!

16
00:03:11,832 --> 00:03:13,083
Fine!

17
00:03:13,266 --> 00:03:14,559
I love you, Jay.

18
00:03:14,584 --> 00:03:16,128
I love you too, Keifer.

19
00:03:16,294 --> 00:03:18,171
I've been thinking about
telling Yuri about us.

20
00:03:18,329 --> 00:03:19,548
It's really Keifer.

21
00:03:19,548 --> 00:03:21,508
I knew from the start it was Keifer.

22
00:03:21,508 --> 00:03:24,094
I just hope you won't regret
choosing him over Yuri.

23
00:03:24,290 --> 00:03:26,012
Section E is divided once again.

24
00:03:26,054 --> 00:03:28,432
Wow, bonding with Jay
like you don't know anything!

25
00:03:28,432 --> 00:03:29,725
- What?!
- Asshole!

26
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:32,043
What's happening,
why are you all fighting?!

27
00:03:32,352 --> 00:03:34,146
You'll regret being with Keifer.

28
00:03:34,146 --> 00:03:34,980
Trust me.

29
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:36,273
I've been there.

30
00:03:36,356 --> 00:03:37,566
You're so pretty, huh.

31
00:03:37,566 --> 00:03:38,567
Freya, stop it!

32
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:41,319
I want to see your reaction

33
00:03:41,319 --> 00:03:42,654
when you find out—

34
00:03:42,654 --> 00:03:43,572
Hey!

35
00:03:43,572 --> 00:03:45,157
what those two did to me.

36
00:03:45,282 --> 00:03:47,546
Yuri was the first one who came to me.

37
00:03:47,571 --> 00:03:48,910
And he left me.

38
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:50,328
Then Keifer showed up.

39
00:03:50,328 --> 00:03:52,080
He laid a hand on me.

40
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:54,545
Did you really hurt Freya?

41
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:55,876
I did.

42
00:03:55,876 --> 00:03:58,837
Remember what you told me before?

43
00:03:58,837 --> 00:04:02,299
That I need to forgive you
even if you guys did me dirty.

44
00:04:02,299 --> 00:04:03,467
Truth or dare?

45
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:04,554
How about this, Yuri.

46
00:04:04,579 --> 00:04:06,219
When are you planning to tell us

47
00:04:06,219 --> 00:04:08,096
about your engagement to Jay-jay?

48
00:04:08,096 --> 00:04:08,722
Huh?!

49
00:04:08,722 --> 00:04:10,453
Well, fuck! What else
do we not know?

50
00:04:10,478 --> 00:04:11,562
Eren, hey!

51
00:04:11,975 --> 00:04:13,643
Enough! That's enough!

52
00:04:21,509 --> 00:04:23,135
<i>Until now...</i>

53
00:04:23,442 --> 00:04:26,696
<i> I still can't believe </i>
<i>that Aries is my brother.</i>

54
00:04:27,139 --> 00:04:29,934
Until now, Jay-jay still
doesn't know the truth?

55
00:04:30,226 --> 00:04:32,937
You still haven't told Jay-jay
that you guys are siblings?

56
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:35,773
You didn't know Aries is your brother?

57
00:04:36,782 --> 00:04:39,159
<i>How can they even hide that from me?</i>

58
00:04:39,979 --> 00:04:41,230
<i>If they really love me,</i>

59
00:04:41,719 --> 00:04:43,512
<i>why did they have to lie?</i>

60
00:04:44,106 --> 00:04:45,107
Aries!

61
00:04:45,914 --> 00:04:47,081
Who is he?

62
00:04:47,261 --> 00:04:48,619
He's my cousin.

63
00:04:48,619 --> 00:04:50,287
I'll play with him first, okay?

64
00:04:50,454 --> 00:04:51,872
She's my cousin.

65
00:04:52,456 --> 00:04:53,541
But that doesn't mean

66
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:55,876
she has immunity from
whatever you want to do to her.

67
00:04:57,791 --> 00:05:00,544
Jay, can you talk to your cousin for me?

68
00:05:00,569 --> 00:05:01,946
Tell him to come home.

69
00:05:01,971 --> 00:05:03,389
Good evening, Aries.

70
00:05:10,474 --> 00:05:12,101
<i>Do they really love me?</i>

71
00:05:14,729 --> 00:05:16,272
<i>It hurts when you find out </i>

72
00:05:16,272 --> 00:05:19,025
<i>that the people closest to you</i>
<i>have been keeping secrets from you.</i>

73
00:05:20,693 --> 00:05:22,611
<i>When they lie to you.</i>

74
00:05:36,584 --> 00:05:39,128
Jay-jay, you don't know
that Aries is your brother?

75
00:06:14,497 --> 00:06:15,456
It's okay.

76
00:06:20,127 --> 00:06:23,255
<i>A few days have passed </i>
<i>since they cut the retreat short.</i>

77
00:06:24,924 --> 00:06:26,926
Because of you,
our section was ruined!

78
00:06:28,469 --> 00:06:29,804
'Cause I miss you.

79
00:06:29,804 --> 00:06:31,055
I miss you too.

80
00:06:31,055 --> 00:06:33,557
That you're the one
I loved, and not Keifer!

81
00:06:33,849 --> 00:06:35,101
- Aries, stop!
- Aries.

82
00:06:37,561 --> 00:06:39,772
You knew about this
and didn't care enough to tell me?

83
00:06:44,193 --> 00:06:47,029
It wasn't my grandfather
who set up the engagement.

84
00:06:47,571 --> 00:06:48,322
What?

85
00:06:48,531 --> 00:06:50,282
I was the one who
arranged our engagement.

86
00:06:50,384 --> 00:06:52,010
That's not love.

87
00:06:52,035 --> 00:06:53,245
That's your ego.

88
00:06:53,514 --> 00:06:54,599
You're not saving me,

89
00:06:54,624 --> 00:06:56,084
you're just selfish.

90
00:06:56,453 --> 00:06:57,646
Keifer.

91
00:06:59,531 --> 00:07:01,533
I'll pretend I didn't see anything.

92
00:07:07,091 --> 00:07:10,094
<i>Keifer still hasn't
talked to me since then.</i>

93
00:07:10,886 --> 00:07:12,304
<i>Is he still mad?</i>

94
00:07:27,687 --> 00:07:29,772
What should I do?

95
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,551
<i>Oh my God, Jay-jay!</i>

96
00:09:14,969 --> 00:09:17,054
<i>Your feet brought you here again!</i>

97
00:09:20,849 --> 00:09:22,142
<i>Fine, whatever.</i>

98
00:09:23,709 --> 00:09:25,502
<i>What are you going to say? </i>

99
00:09:25,527 --> 00:09:27,112
<i>Is this right?</i>

100
00:09:27,731 --> 00:09:29,441
<i>Wait, think about it first...</i>

101
00:09:30,190 --> 00:09:31,656
<i>but you're already here anyway!</i>

102
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,508
Jay.

103
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:43,752
<i>Jay, why did you even come here?</i>

104
00:09:43,777 --> 00:09:45,153
<i>So crazy!</i>

105
00:09:46,492 --> 00:09:47,805
What are you doing here?

106
00:09:51,146 --> 00:09:53,481
Is Keifer there?

107
00:09:54,216 --> 00:09:55,676
Sorry. He's not home.

108
00:09:56,093 --> 00:09:57,219
He went out.

109
00:09:57,303 --> 00:09:58,383
Ah.

110
00:09:58,595 --> 00:09:59,742
Is that so?

111
00:09:59,821 --> 00:10:01,198
But, when he comes home,

112
00:10:01,223 --> 00:10:02,307
I'll tell him to call you.

113
00:10:03,765 --> 00:10:05,850
Okay, thank you.

114
00:10:06,312 --> 00:10:07,422
Okay.

115
00:10:17,254 --> 00:10:19,715
Keifer, where are you?

116
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:39,405
Did something happen?

117
00:10:39,469 --> 00:10:40,720
Nothing.

118
00:10:40,859 --> 00:10:42,235
Your girlfriend passed by.

119
00:10:42,945 --> 00:10:44,071
Why did she come?

120
00:10:44,116 --> 00:10:45,242
Did anything happen to her?

121
00:10:45,267 --> 00:10:46,310
What did she say?

122
00:10:46,393 --> 00:10:47,519
Relax bro,

123
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,643
nothing important.

124
00:10:48,668 --> 00:10:49,836
She was just looking for you.

125
00:10:51,635 --> 00:10:53,888
Just don't say anything
that's gonna make her worry.

126
00:10:54,683 --> 00:10:55,627
Sure.

127
00:10:55,652 --> 00:10:57,696
Just stay focused on
your goal there in London.

128
00:10:59,366 --> 00:11:00,433
Okay.

129
00:11:21,053 --> 00:11:22,388
I'm sorry, Jay.

130
00:11:23,145 --> 00:11:24,397
I gotta stay focused.

131
00:11:24,988 --> 00:11:27,191
You're gonna have
to wait a little bit longer.

132
00:11:47,454 --> 00:11:48,543
Angelo.

133
00:11:49,248 --> 00:11:51,917
You could've at least
told me where we're going,

134
00:11:52,126 --> 00:11:53,877
instead of surprising me like this.

135
00:11:55,402 --> 00:11:56,528
I'm sorry, Jay.

136
00:11:56,630 --> 00:11:58,090
She wants to do it today.

137
00:11:58,315 --> 00:12:00,025
So, I had to rush you.

138
00:12:04,972 --> 00:12:06,223
Hi.

139
00:12:08,033 --> 00:12:09,534
Hi guys.

140
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:10,612
Hello.

141
00:12:10,637 --> 00:12:13,640
Jay, thank you so much
for being here.

142
00:12:13,665 --> 00:12:16,620
Angelo, thank you so much
for dropping her.

143
00:12:16,645 --> 00:12:18,564
Anytime, Mrs. Hanamitchi.

144
00:12:19,236 --> 00:12:20,654
For now, I'll leave you two here.

145
00:12:20,679 --> 00:12:23,464
- Okay.
- Just call me when you're done.

146
00:12:23,489 --> 00:12:24,323
Alright.

147
00:12:24,348 --> 00:12:25,308
Okay.

148
00:12:25,362 --> 00:12:26,905
I'll take care of her.

149
00:12:33,701 --> 00:12:35,661
Are you okay, Jay?

150
00:12:36,834 --> 00:12:38,336
I'm okay.

151
00:12:38,361 --> 00:12:40,238
I'm sorry if I rushed you, okay?

152
00:12:40,263 --> 00:12:44,058
I just want us to
have enough time to prepare.

153
00:12:47,420 --> 00:12:50,131
How is Yuri?

154
00:12:50,131 --> 00:12:51,882
Okay. He's fine.

155
00:12:51,882 --> 00:12:55,469
He finally recovered from
the flu he got in your retreat.

156
00:12:55,469 --> 00:12:56,721
Oh, do you want to see him?

157
00:13:00,224 --> 00:13:04,020
- Mrs. Hanamitchi.
- Oh! Gertrude.

158
00:13:05,187 --> 00:13:07,690
- How are you?
- I'm doing well.

159
00:13:07,815 --> 00:13:10,901
Still pretty as ever.

160
00:13:10,985 --> 00:13:12,820
Thank you.

161
00:13:17,136 --> 00:13:18,346
[ In Japanese ]

162
00:13:19,795 --> 00:13:20,921
[ In Japanese ]

163
00:13:23,831 --> 00:13:26,000
<i>Huh? Did he curse at me?</i>

164
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:28,002
So pretty, right?

165
00:13:31,047 --> 00:13:32,106
Okay.

166
00:13:32,131 --> 00:13:33,215
Let's fit the gown.

167
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:35,587
That one first.

168
00:13:36,677 --> 00:13:38,888
So beautiful!

169
00:13:38,913 --> 00:13:42,109
Of course, Mrs. Hanamitchi.
You know me so well.

170
00:13:58,199 --> 00:13:59,617
Presenting...

171
00:13:59,617 --> 00:14:00,951
my masterpiece.

172
00:14:00,993 --> 00:14:02,620
Oh, wow!

173
00:14:02,620 --> 00:14:06,165
Gertrude, you've outdone yourself.

174
00:14:06,165 --> 00:14:08,584
It's so beautiful.

175
00:14:08,584 --> 00:14:09,377
I know.

176
00:14:09,377 --> 00:14:10,586
You're welcome.

177
00:14:12,004 --> 00:14:13,619
So, I'll leave you two to it. Okay?

178
00:14:17,676 --> 00:14:18,969
Well?

179
00:14:19,970 --> 00:14:21,680
Do you like it?

180
00:14:24,183 --> 00:14:26,035
That's what you'll be wearing....

181
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:28,119
to your wedding with Yuri.

182
00:14:28,144 --> 00:14:29,854
It's your wedding gown.

183
00:14:32,108 --> 00:14:35,236
<i>So this is how it feels </i>
<i>to try on a wedding gown.</i>

184
00:14:35,855 --> 00:14:38,065
<i>It's exciting, and romantic.</i>

185
00:14:38,408 --> 00:14:39,824
I'll take a picture later.

186
00:14:39,824 --> 00:14:41,409
I'll send it to Yuri.

187
00:14:41,409 --> 00:14:43,619
Oh, he'll be so happy!

188
00:14:44,203 --> 00:14:48,197
<i>But when I think about the fact that</i>
<i>I'm about to marry someone I don't love...</i>

189
00:14:48,579 --> 00:14:50,572
<i>Someone who lied to me.</i>

190
00:14:51,769 --> 00:14:53,728
<i>Someone I trusted.</i>

191
00:14:54,422 --> 00:14:58,447
<i>Someone I thought was also just</i>
<i>a victim of their family's nonsense.</i>

192
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:02,408
Don't you like it?

193
00:15:05,528 --> 00:15:07,030
I like it.

194
00:15:12,936 --> 00:15:14,146
You know...

195
00:15:16,444 --> 00:15:18,195
honestly,

196
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:23,534
I don't want you to be my daughter-in-law.

197
00:15:26,954 --> 00:15:29,498
I just really love Yuri.

198
00:15:30,249 --> 00:15:34,336
I'm willing to give
up everything for him.

199
00:15:35,796 --> 00:15:37,590
I understand you.

200
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:40,718
Yuri's dad and I also had
an arranged marriage.

201
00:15:42,052 --> 00:15:46,182
And the whole Hanamitchi clan
didn't like me.

202
00:15:47,349 --> 00:15:50,603
I did everything to prove my worth.

203
00:15:51,353 --> 00:15:53,731
To make them like me, but...

204
00:15:54,315 --> 00:15:55,441
No.

205
00:15:57,193 --> 00:15:58,444
They didn't accept me.

206
00:16:02,198 --> 00:16:03,616
Until...

207
00:16:04,617 --> 00:16:05,993
Yuri came.

208
00:16:09,455 --> 00:16:12,249
And they were so happy.

209
00:16:13,501 --> 00:16:15,794
They said Yuri's lucky.

210
00:16:17,463 --> 00:16:19,465
I gave birth to him when

211
00:16:19,465 --> 00:16:22,009
the family business was failing.

212
00:16:23,844 --> 00:16:28,057
And he was such a blessing.

213
00:16:30,392 --> 00:16:33,562
He was so funny, so cute.

214
00:16:34,355 --> 00:16:36,232
He was smart.

215
00:16:37,066 --> 00:16:38,692
He was always happy.

216
00:16:40,027 --> 00:16:42,571
I gave him everything,

217
00:16:42,571 --> 00:16:46,575
even if he never asked for anything.

218
00:16:48,202 --> 00:16:49,370
But then...

219
00:16:51,330 --> 00:16:53,832
He introduced me to Ella.

220
00:16:56,752 --> 00:16:58,837
And things changed.

221
00:17:02,591 --> 00:17:04,468
I didn't like Ella.

222
00:17:05,344 --> 00:17:08,097
Because she wasn't
pure Japanese and I knew.

223
00:17:08,722 --> 00:17:11,934
I knew the Hanamitchi clan
wouldn't allow it.

224
00:17:12,518 --> 00:17:14,103
I was scared.

225
00:17:15,145 --> 00:17:17,356
I did what I thought was right.

226
00:17:17,356 --> 00:17:19,942
I talked to Keifer and told him

227
00:17:20,693 --> 00:17:23,112
to keep Ella away from Yuri.

228
00:17:25,197 --> 00:17:26,865
I didn't know that...

229
00:17:28,826 --> 00:17:32,079
they were already
fighting over one girl.

230
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,293
When Yuri came home,
he was a different person.

231
00:17:39,753 --> 00:17:41,338
He dyed his hair.

232
00:17:43,299 --> 00:17:45,009
He was always drunk.

233
00:17:45,926 --> 00:17:47,553
Always picking fights.

234
00:17:47,553 --> 00:17:48,429
We were...

235
00:17:48,971 --> 00:17:49,597
We were...

236
00:17:49,597 --> 00:17:50,556
in shock.

237
00:17:53,976 --> 00:17:55,644
But because of you...

238
00:17:57,021 --> 00:17:58,772
because of you, Jay.

239
00:18:02,401 --> 00:18:05,195
I'm starting to see my old Yuri again.

240
00:18:07,489 --> 00:18:09,116
And I promised myself,

241
00:18:10,159 --> 00:18:13,579
I will not repeat
the same mistake twice.

242
00:18:14,538 --> 00:18:18,250
I will do everything
to make my son happy.

243
00:18:21,253 --> 00:18:22,671
So please...

244
00:18:24,715 --> 00:18:26,175
Please.

245
00:18:29,178 --> 00:18:30,846
Love my son.

246
00:18:34,892 --> 00:18:36,685
Love my son.

247
00:18:39,813 --> 00:18:42,691
I can't bear to see
him miserable again.

248
00:18:44,068 --> 00:18:45,361
Please, Jay.

249
00:18:47,154 --> 00:18:48,530
I beg you.

250
00:18:51,992 --> 00:18:53,535
Love my son.

251
00:18:55,496 --> 00:18:56,497
Please.

252
00:18:59,625 --> 00:19:00,959
Please.

253
00:19:03,712 --> 00:19:05,631
Please.

254
00:19:05,631 --> 00:19:07,424
Please, love my son.

255
00:19:08,717 --> 00:19:10,260
<i>Even if I wanted to...</i>

256
00:19:11,303 --> 00:19:13,013
<i>I'm in love with someone else. </i>

257
00:19:39,415 --> 00:19:40,582
Why did she call?

258
00:19:40,582 --> 00:19:41,709
Did anything happen to her?

259
00:19:41,709 --> 00:19:43,711
Relax, bro. Nothing important.

260
00:19:43,913 --> 00:19:46,457
Just don’t say anything that’s
gonna make her worry.

261
00:19:54,471 --> 00:19:57,099
Jay, in the future

262
00:19:57,975 --> 00:20:00,686
just ask me. Okay?

263
00:20:00,686 --> 00:20:03,147
I will try my best to
give you the answers.

264
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:16,660
<i>You can’t stop the </i>
<i>wedding, so back off.</i>

265
00:20:21,457 --> 00:20:24,168
<i>I'm going to get you back, Jay.</i>

266
00:20:24,168 --> 00:20:26,211
<i>Please, wait for me.</i>

267
00:20:26,211 --> 00:20:28,255
<i>I'm coming.</i>

268
00:20:39,308 --> 00:20:40,684
Grandma!

269
00:20:40,726 --> 00:20:43,479
Oh, you're already here.

270
00:20:43,479 --> 00:20:45,063
- I missed you.
- Oh, you!

271
00:20:45,063 --> 00:20:47,900
- It's so late, why were you still outside?
- Hi, Grandma.

272
00:20:50,235 --> 00:20:54,364
Angelo took me to Yuri's mom.

273
00:20:57,743 --> 00:20:59,453
Wow, my daughter's so sweet.

274
00:20:59,745 --> 00:21:01,038
Don't I get a hug, too?

275
00:21:08,796 --> 00:21:10,756
Jay-jay, I'm waiting.

276
00:21:13,842 --> 00:21:14,863
Come on.

277
00:21:23,936 --> 00:21:25,020
How are you?

278
00:21:25,604 --> 00:21:27,147
We haven't talked much lately.

279
00:21:27,147 --> 00:21:28,649
What's been happening to you?

280
00:21:29,817 --> 00:21:30,776
Everything's fine.

281
00:21:31,318 --> 00:21:32,736
How are your studies?

282
00:21:34,488 --> 00:21:35,488
Fine as well.

283
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,159
Hon.

284
00:21:40,953 --> 00:21:42,287
This is Jay-jay.

285
00:21:42,287 --> 00:21:43,497
She's my daughter.

286
00:21:44,540 --> 00:21:45,582
This is for you.

287
00:22:00,305 --> 00:22:03,183
Jay-jay, this is Andy.

288
00:22:03,183 --> 00:22:06,562
We're getting married,
so he's going to be your new dad.

289
00:22:07,938 --> 00:22:09,231
Nice to meet you, Jay-jay.

290
00:22:14,987 --> 00:22:17,781
Jay, introduce yourself properly.

291
00:22:20,325 --> 00:22:21,660
I'm Jay-jay.

292
00:22:22,494 --> 00:22:24,037
Thank you for the gift.

293
00:22:29,209 --> 00:22:30,335
You're welcome.

294
00:22:30,335 --> 00:22:32,726
Just tell me if there's
anything else you want.

295
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:37,276
<i>I'm scared.</i>

296
00:22:37,301 --> 00:22:40,637
<i>This is the same feeling </i>
<i>I had back then with Tony Dela Cruz...</i>

297
00:22:40,637 --> 00:22:42,097
Let me apologize to you,

298
00:22:42,264 --> 00:22:43,640
for the wrong things I did

299
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,492
when I was still married to your mom.

300
00:22:45,517 --> 00:22:47,060
In case you don't remember me,

301
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:49,104
- Tony Dela Cruz.
- I'm sorry.

302
00:22:49,229 --> 00:22:51,148
I really don't remember.
I'll go ahead.

303
00:22:53,859 --> 00:22:54,902
Jay-jay.

304
00:22:57,613 --> 00:22:59,320
Jay, are you okay?

305
00:23:03,827 --> 00:23:04,828
Jay.

306
00:23:10,375 --> 00:23:12,252
You know, it might
be better if we have dinner first.

307
00:23:12,252 --> 00:23:14,046
Mom? Aren't you hungry?

308
00:23:14,046 --> 00:23:15,464
Go ahead.

309
00:23:15,464 --> 00:23:17,215
We'll follow. Jay and I will follow.

310
00:23:17,215 --> 00:23:18,508
I'll just talk to her.

311
00:23:18,508 --> 00:23:19,426
Okay.

312
00:23:19,509 --> 00:23:20,515
Jay,

313
00:23:21,386 --> 00:23:22,531
we'll see you at dinner, okay?

314
00:23:23,889 --> 00:23:24,922
Go ahead.

315
00:23:37,323 --> 00:23:38,976
What's with your attitude?

316
00:23:39,237 --> 00:23:41,698
Why did you act
that way towards Andy?

317
00:23:42,370 --> 00:23:43,412
Please,

318
00:23:43,991 --> 00:23:45,284
just go away.

319
00:23:47,245 --> 00:23:48,305
Jay-jay.

320
00:23:48,789 --> 00:23:51,375
I'm trying to fix things between us.

321
00:23:52,376 --> 00:23:53,752
But if you keep treating me this way,

322
00:23:53,752 --> 00:23:56,297
I don't care if you're 17.
I'll still discipline you.

323
00:23:56,546 --> 00:23:59,226
Whether you like it or not,
Andy and I are getting married.

324
00:23:59,251 --> 00:24:02,838
He will be your new father
and we'll be a family.

325
00:24:04,137 --> 00:24:05,140
Wow.

326
00:24:05,931 --> 00:24:07,015
A family.

327
00:24:07,849 --> 00:24:08,930
Big word.

328
00:24:09,101 --> 00:24:10,180
What did you say?

329
00:24:11,269 --> 00:24:12,273
Nothing.

330
00:24:21,405 --> 00:24:23,407
Ma'am, you have a visitor.

331
00:24:24,116 --> 00:24:25,117
Hi, Jay.

332
00:24:25,283 --> 00:24:26,289
Yuri?

333
00:24:30,867 --> 00:24:33,203
And who is this handsome young man?

334
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:34,334
Good evening.

335
00:24:34,334 --> 00:24:35,585
I'm Yuri Hanamitchi.

336
00:24:39,381 --> 00:24:41,591
So you're my daughter's husband-to-be?

337
00:24:42,050 --> 00:24:43,086
Yes.

338
00:24:43,385 --> 00:24:45,470
You can call me mom.

339
00:24:48,098 --> 00:24:49,599
What are you doing here?

340
00:24:50,517 --> 00:24:51,893
Angelo texted me earlier.

341
00:24:51,893 --> 00:24:53,562
He said your mom
wants to meet me.

342
00:24:53,937 --> 00:24:56,231
I also wanted to meet her, so I came.

343
00:25:00,027 --> 00:25:02,612
Come, join us for dinner,

344
00:25:02,612 --> 00:25:05,532
so you can also meet your new family.

345
00:25:05,532 --> 00:25:06,544
Okay, ma'am.

346
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:13,999
Have you eaten dinner, Yuri?

347
00:25:13,999 --> 00:25:16,793
Perfect, I haven’t eaten yet.

348
00:25:16,793 --> 00:25:18,211
<i>Jay-jay, breathe.</i>

349
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,047
<i>Calm down.</i>

350
00:25:20,589 --> 00:25:23,884
<i>Don't let your mom </i>
<i>ruin your peaceful mind again.</i>

351
00:25:24,551 --> 00:25:25,969
<i>Calm down.</i>

352
00:25:33,935 --> 00:25:36,772
Ma'am, you have another visitor.

353
00:25:38,648 --> 00:25:40,108
Son of a—

354
00:25:58,460 --> 00:25:59,544
Keifer?

355
00:26:02,005 --> 00:26:03,131
I missed you.

356
00:26:04,674 --> 00:26:06,093
Why are you here?

357
00:26:06,968 --> 00:26:08,845
They might see you.

358
00:26:09,763 --> 00:26:11,973
What happened to you?
Where did you go?

359
00:26:12,432 --> 00:26:13,441
London.

360
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,605
London?

361
00:26:15,936 --> 00:26:16,949
London.

362
00:26:17,813 --> 00:26:18,855
England.

363
00:26:19,397 --> 00:26:20,524
The UK.

364
00:26:21,608 --> 00:26:22,644
What did you do there?

365
00:26:23,151 --> 00:26:24,444
I met with my cousins.

366
00:26:26,363 --> 00:26:28,406
Can you explain it to me more clearly?

367
00:26:33,453 --> 00:26:34,663
It's about Kaizer.

368
00:26:35,455 --> 00:26:36,464
My father.

369
00:26:37,165 --> 00:26:39,543
I met up with my
relatives and cousins,

370
00:26:39,543 --> 00:26:42,420
hoping to find somebody
who will be willing to help us.

371
00:26:43,171 --> 00:26:43,964
But...

372
00:26:43,964 --> 00:26:44,964
they refused.

373
00:26:46,466 --> 00:26:47,634
How come?

374
00:26:49,302 --> 00:26:51,680
Watsons don't move unless
there's something in it for them.

375
00:26:56,810 --> 00:26:58,645
Why were you not replying?

376
00:26:59,479 --> 00:27:01,314
I wish you had
told me what was going on.

377
00:27:03,775 --> 00:27:05,318
Are you still mad at me?

378
00:27:05,861 --> 00:27:07,445
I was worried about you.

379
00:27:07,571 --> 00:27:09,948
Jay, I'm sorry.
I had to stay focused.

380
00:27:10,407 --> 00:27:13,535
Because if I had read your texts,
if I had heard your voice,

381
00:27:14,286 --> 00:27:16,246
I would've come home
right away just to see you.

382
00:27:16,663 --> 00:27:18,206
Did you just get back?

383
00:27:18,331 --> 00:27:20,750
Yeah. And I came straight here.

384
00:27:20,750 --> 00:27:22,294
Because I really...

385
00:27:22,711 --> 00:27:25,046
Really needed to see you.

386
00:27:29,134 --> 00:27:30,802
Are you excited, Yuri?

387
00:27:30,802 --> 00:27:32,679
Yes, I'm very much excited.

388
00:27:32,679 --> 00:27:34,556
Oh, I mean, mom.

389
00:27:34,556 --> 00:27:35,640
Oh wow.

390
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:38,018
You know, I'm excited too
because I'm also engaged.

391
00:27:38,268 --> 00:27:39,060
I knew it!

392
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:40,478
I knew he was here.

393
00:27:40,645 --> 00:27:42,564
I knew he was gonna
make moves without me around.

394
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:43,815
Let's go.

395
00:27:43,815 --> 00:27:45,066
Hey! Wait a minute.

396
00:27:46,234 --> 00:27:48,153
That's good. That's good.

397
00:27:56,036 --> 00:27:57,412
Good evening, everyone.

398
00:27:57,704 --> 00:27:58,580
Well!

399
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:01,583
And who is this other
handsome gentleman?

400
00:28:02,167 --> 00:28:02,959
Hi.

401
00:28:02,959 --> 00:28:04,669
Uhm, you're Jay-jay's?

402
00:28:05,221 --> 00:28:06,222
Mother.

403
00:28:06,504 --> 00:28:08,256
Mother? Are you sure?

404
00:28:08,256 --> 00:28:10,175
You could pass as her sister.

405
00:28:13,762 --> 00:28:16,556
By the way, sorry.
I'm Mark Keifer Watson.

406
00:28:16,556 --> 00:28:17,766
Watson?

407
00:28:18,266 --> 00:28:20,685
No wonder you have such charisma.

408
00:28:21,394 --> 00:28:22,938
Would you like to join us for dinner?

409
00:28:23,438 --> 00:28:24,731
Is it okay, Yuri?

410
00:28:25,273 --> 00:28:26,691
Keifer's a friend of mine.

411
00:28:26,775 --> 00:28:29,069
So it's fine with me, mom.

412
00:28:32,364 --> 00:28:33,531
Okay.

413
00:28:34,407 --> 00:28:35,700
Go ahead.

414
00:28:35,825 --> 00:28:36,826
Thank you.

415
00:28:39,037 --> 00:28:40,747
Uhm, yeah let's eat.

416
00:28:41,338 --> 00:28:42,740
- The food is good.
- Mom, eat.

417
00:28:42,891 --> 00:28:43,998
Thank you.

418
00:28:52,259 --> 00:28:55,387
- Jay, eat some vegatables.
- I'll just have this.

419
00:28:58,265 --> 00:29:00,850
I'll take the vegetables.
You don't eat these anyway.

420
00:29:01,643 --> 00:29:05,730
Just eat, okay?
We still have plenty more.

421
00:29:06,481 --> 00:29:08,942
- Do you want some ham?
- Here's some rice.

422
00:29:10,986 --> 00:29:12,612
Go ahead, grab some food.

423
00:29:12,821 --> 00:29:13,868
Thanks, mom.

424
00:29:17,951 --> 00:29:19,035
Thank you.

425
00:29:23,206 --> 00:29:26,126
My bad! I forgot to ask if
you wanted some chicken.

426
00:29:27,752 --> 00:29:29,629
So, what are you doing here, Keifer?

427
00:29:34,342 --> 00:29:35,719
I came to see Jay-jay.

428
00:29:41,057 --> 00:29:42,100
Why?

429
00:29:45,687 --> 00:29:47,063
There's no reason.

430
00:29:49,065 --> 00:29:52,319
Keifer, what's the deal
between you and Jay-jay?

431
00:29:52,485 --> 00:29:53,737
Well, Uncle...

432
00:29:54,404 --> 00:29:55,488
Mom,

433
00:29:57,531 --> 00:29:58,949
He will be my best man.

434
00:30:01,077 --> 00:30:02,078
No,

435
00:30:02,454 --> 00:30:04,247
he will be my best man.

436
00:30:04,998 --> 00:30:05,999
Sure.

437
00:30:06,499 --> 00:30:07,917
Just let me know when,

438
00:30:07,917 --> 00:30:10,295
so I can make sure
Jay and I can attend.

439
00:30:10,503 --> 00:30:11,582
Of course.

440
00:30:11,713 --> 00:30:14,049
Just make sure Jay-jay will be there.

441
00:30:14,507 --> 00:30:17,218
It would be awkward
if my bride didn't show up.

442
00:30:17,218 --> 00:30:18,386
Wait, I’m confused.

443
00:30:19,054 --> 00:30:20,221
Excuse me?

444
00:30:20,430 --> 00:30:21,890
What the hell is going on?

445
00:30:22,265 --> 00:30:23,975
Consider this your invitation.

446
00:30:23,975 --> 00:30:25,560
Everyone is welcome at the wedding.

447
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:27,145
Angelo, what is happening?

448
00:30:27,312 --> 00:30:28,313
Jay-jay!

449
00:30:28,313 --> 00:30:29,652
What is your relationship with Keifer?

450
00:30:29,898 --> 00:30:30,690
What the hell, Keifer!

451
00:30:30,690 --> 00:30:34,319
- Uh, well...
- We're more than friends,

452
00:30:34,319 --> 00:30:37,322
but not less than lovers.

453
00:30:39,324 --> 00:30:40,367
What?!

454
00:30:40,784 --> 00:30:42,035
Since when?

455
00:30:43,828 --> 00:30:45,205
Angelo, relax.

456
00:30:45,205 --> 00:30:47,165
Just relax, okay? Relax.

457
00:30:47,207 --> 00:30:48,375
Relax?!

458
00:30:48,375 --> 00:30:49,667
How am I supposed to do that?

459
00:30:55,090 --> 00:30:57,050
[phone buzzing]

460
00:30:58,593 --> 00:30:59,928
[phone buzzing]

461
00:31:03,431 --> 00:31:05,058
What happened to Aries?

462
00:31:06,434 --> 00:31:07,727
Aries?

463
00:31:09,646 --> 00:31:10,686
We'll be there.

464
00:31:11,189 --> 00:31:12,857
What happened to Aries?

465
00:31:12,941 --> 00:31:14,192
We'll figure it out there.

466
00:31:14,275 --> 00:31:16,444
- What happened?
- Wait, I'm coming too.

467
00:31:16,569 --> 00:31:19,280
- I'll drive.
- Mom, we're just going to see Aries.

468
00:31:19,656 --> 00:31:22,158
What happened?

469
00:31:25,537 --> 00:31:27,372
<i>I wonder what happened to Aries...</i>

470
00:31:28,581 --> 00:31:31,000
<i>Even my mom is panicking and </i>
<i>rushing to go see him.</i>

471
00:31:31,709 --> 00:31:33,378
<i>Hopefully, it’s nothing serious.</i>

472
00:31:33,711 --> 00:31:34,712
I'm sure...

473
00:31:36,005 --> 00:31:37,757
Aries is gonna be okay.

474
00:31:40,343 --> 00:31:41,094
Jay-jay.

475
00:31:43,263 --> 00:31:44,556
What's the truth?

476
00:31:45,849 --> 00:31:47,058
Answer me.

477
00:31:49,853 --> 00:31:51,104
Grandma, it's because...

478
00:31:51,396 --> 00:31:52,772
They have a relationship.

479
00:31:54,441 --> 00:31:56,109
Even though we're engaged.

480
00:32:02,115 --> 00:32:03,491
You allowed it?

481
00:32:04,409 --> 00:32:06,411
We're not married yet, Grandma.

482
00:32:07,454 --> 00:32:09,956
And he can't stop us either.

483
00:32:12,459 --> 00:32:14,627
I'm in love with
your granddaughter.

484
00:32:21,885 --> 00:32:23,887
You fix this, Jay-jay.

485
00:32:25,430 --> 00:32:27,515
You're trying to have it both ways.

486
00:32:27,974 --> 00:32:29,100
Is that right?

487
00:32:29,767 --> 00:32:31,436
Please don't blame Jay-jay for this.

488
00:32:32,562 --> 00:32:34,355
She's just being pressured by Yuri.

489
00:32:37,192 --> 00:32:38,776
We're really the official couple.

490
00:32:38,818 --> 00:32:39,777
Official?

491
00:32:40,028 --> 00:32:41,488
You don't even have a label.

492
00:32:43,281 --> 00:32:44,335
Enough.

493
00:32:44,908 --> 00:32:45,929
Jay-jay,

494
00:32:46,451 --> 00:32:48,369
you better make a choice.

495
00:32:48,620 --> 00:32:49,996
You know what's right,

496
00:32:50,205 --> 00:32:51,873
you know what's wrong.

497
00:32:53,791 --> 00:32:55,710
You have a conscience.

498
00:32:57,003 --> 00:32:58,421
Make a decision.

499
00:33:03,301 --> 00:33:04,385
Oh my.

500
00:33:04,385 --> 00:33:05,970
You guys are such a mess.

501
00:33:05,970 --> 00:33:08,389
I might end up getting
rushed to the hospital next!

502
00:33:08,556 --> 00:33:10,391
My blood pressure is rising!

503
00:33:10,725 --> 00:33:12,352
Go home already.

504
00:33:17,732 --> 00:33:19,609
Young people these days.

505
00:33:20,068 --> 00:33:21,653
Oh my goodness!

506
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:41,548
<i>I still don't know </i>
<i>how I survived last night.</i>

507
00:33:49,597 --> 00:33:50,848
What are you doing?

508
00:33:57,272 --> 00:33:58,364
Jay,

509
00:33:59,148 --> 00:34:00,192
are you okay?

510
00:34:05,238 --> 00:34:06,281
Ci.

511
00:34:07,574 --> 00:34:09,117
Pst, Ci!

512
00:34:10,618 --> 00:34:11,744
What happened here?

513
00:34:12,017 --> 00:34:13,393
Haven't you guys made up yet?

514
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:25,383
Jay, I need to talk to you outside.

515
00:34:26,968 --> 00:34:28,678
Please, it's important.

516
00:34:28,678 --> 00:34:30,179
- Okay.
- Let’s go.

517
00:34:38,479 --> 00:34:40,398
What do we need
to talk about, David?

518
00:34:40,732 --> 00:34:42,066
Why does it have to be here?

519
00:34:43,276 --> 00:34:44,110
<i>Hello.</i>

520
00:34:44,110 --> 00:34:45,236
She's with me.

521
00:34:45,236 --> 00:34:46,946
- Huh?
-<i> Is it just the two of you?</i>

522
00:34:47,113 --> 00:34:48,740
<i>I want to talk to her.</i>

523
00:34:49,616 --> 00:34:50,950
He wants to talk to you.

524
00:34:59,959 --> 00:35:01,169
Hello, Percy.

525
00:35:01,878 --> 00:35:04,297
<i>Jay, I’m heading home now.</i>
<i> I can finally answer—</i>

526
00:35:04,297 --> 00:35:05,798
Don't ever show your face to me.

527
00:35:05,882 --> 00:35:07,091
<i>Jay?</i>

528
00:35:07,967 --> 00:35:09,385
You're just causing trouble for me.

529
00:35:09,719 --> 00:35:11,304
You're messing up my life.

530
00:35:11,304 --> 00:35:14,641
<i>Look. I'm sorry. Please. </i>

531
00:35:15,975 --> 00:35:17,518
I don't need your apology.

532
00:35:18,561 --> 00:35:20,730
What I want to
know is who you really are.

533
00:35:20,980 --> 00:35:22,607
Just when I was almost
getting my life together,

534
00:35:22,607 --> 00:35:24,150
you showed up to
mess it all up again.

535
00:35:25,068 --> 00:35:27,820
<i>Jay, I'm only asking </i>
<i>for a few more days. </i>

536
00:35:27,820 --> 00:35:29,072
<i>We'll finally meet!</i>

537
00:35:29,072 --> 00:35:30,990
I don't care!

538
00:35:31,407 --> 00:35:34,285
I'm begging you. If you're only
going to ruin my life, just stop—

539
00:35:34,285 --> 00:35:36,287
<i>Damn it, Jay! Listen to me!</i>

540
00:35:36,829 --> 00:35:39,916
<i>Give me three—</i>
<i>no, two days. </i>

541
00:35:39,916 --> 00:35:43,252
<i>Give me two days and</i>
<i>I'll answer all your questions.</i>

542
00:35:44,837 --> 00:35:45,672
Enough.

543
00:35:46,881 --> 00:35:47,757
Please.

544
00:35:53,304 --> 00:35:54,055
Jay...

545
00:35:55,598 --> 00:35:56,891
Jay, I’m really sorry.

546
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:58,685
What exactly are you to Percy?

547
00:36:08,236 --> 00:36:09,612
We have a contract.

548
00:36:10,613 --> 00:36:12,365
Percy helped with my
girlfriend's treatment.

549
00:36:13,449 --> 00:36:14,826
In return,

550
00:36:16,828 --> 00:36:18,579
I was asked to keep you safe.

551
00:36:22,583 --> 00:36:23,751
Everything is such a mess,

552
00:36:23,751 --> 00:36:26,045
I don't even know
what to do anymore.

553
00:36:29,924 --> 00:36:31,134
Jay.

554
00:36:33,010 --> 00:36:34,387
Everything's so messed up.

555
00:36:34,387 --> 00:36:35,221
Please, Jay.

556
00:36:35,221 --> 00:36:36,271
Please don't cry.

557
00:36:37,390 --> 00:36:38,466
Please.

558
00:36:40,518 --> 00:36:41,544
Please.

559
00:36:44,522 --> 00:36:45,536
Please, Jay.

560
00:36:47,734 --> 00:36:49,277
- Jay, I'm sorry.
- What the hell?

561
00:36:49,277 --> 00:36:50,403
I was caught off guard.

562
00:36:50,403 --> 00:36:52,530
Everything's already messed up,
and now you've made it worse.

563
00:36:52,530 --> 00:36:54,449
You fucking bastard!

564
00:36:54,782 --> 00:36:55,778
Keifer.

565
00:36:57,535 --> 00:36:58,953
Keifer, enough.

566
00:36:58,978 --> 00:37:00,563
David, just leave!

567
00:37:01,622 --> 00:37:03,082
Leave!

568
00:37:03,624 --> 00:37:04,751
Are you hiding this?

569
00:37:04,917 --> 00:37:06,536
Are you in a relationship with David?

570
00:37:07,170 --> 00:37:08,212
Keifer, no.

571
00:37:08,212 --> 00:37:09,927
Then what are you doing here?!

572
00:37:10,089 --> 00:37:11,007
David just wanted to—

573
00:37:11,007 --> 00:37:12,258
Don't fucking lie to me.

574
00:37:12,592 --> 00:37:13,342
It was Percy!

575
00:37:13,342 --> 00:37:14,677
I was talking to Percy.

576
00:37:14,677 --> 00:37:16,053
Did that include the kiss?

577
00:37:17,013 --> 00:37:19,599
Why are you like this?
Why don't you believe me?

578
00:37:22,025 --> 00:37:23,151
Isn't Yuri enough?

579
00:37:24,395 --> 00:37:26,189
Are you just playing with us?

580
00:37:26,939 --> 00:37:29,025
Keifer, no. Nothing happened.

581
00:37:29,275 --> 00:37:30,610
Don't fucking touch me.

582
00:37:30,610 --> 00:37:32,653
Don't come any closer, Jay.

583
00:37:35,281 --> 00:37:36,824
I might hurt you.

584
00:38:08,689 --> 00:38:10,566
Mom, the paint's getting old

585
00:38:10,566 --> 00:38:12,068
maybe you want to have it renovated.

586
00:38:12,068 --> 00:38:13,444
It’s still alright.

587
00:38:13,444 --> 00:38:16,155
<i>Keifer still hasn't talked to me</i>
<i>after what happened.</i>

588
00:38:16,155 --> 00:38:19,033
He can do it!
Andy can handle that, right, hon?

589
00:38:19,033 --> 00:38:21,494
We can lower the cost.

590
00:38:23,621 --> 00:38:24,634
Jay-jay.

591
00:38:25,873 --> 00:38:26,985
Jay.

592
00:38:27,208 --> 00:38:28,876
Aries is on his way.

593
00:38:29,001 --> 00:38:30,461
He's being discharged today.

594
00:38:30,711 --> 00:38:32,004
Oh, really?

595
00:38:32,004 --> 00:38:33,965
- Yes.
- That's great.

596
00:38:35,967 --> 00:38:37,844
Oh, he must be here.

597
00:38:38,052 --> 00:38:39,804
Mom, we're home.

598
00:38:48,729 --> 00:38:49,897
Aries.

599
00:38:49,897 --> 00:38:51,190
What are you doing here?

600
00:38:53,818 --> 00:38:54,902
We'll be staying here for now.

601
00:38:54,902 --> 00:38:57,613
By the way, this is Andy.
He's the one I told you about.

602
00:38:57,780 --> 00:38:58,865
Andy, this is Aries.

603
00:38:58,865 --> 00:38:59,991
- Hi, Aries.
- Why?

604
00:39:02,326 --> 00:39:03,803
Gemma,

605
00:39:03,828 --> 00:39:06,998
is this what you teach
my kids while I'm not around?

606
00:39:09,208 --> 00:39:10,585
Your kids?

607
00:39:16,591 --> 00:39:18,217
Jeana,

608
00:39:18,384 --> 00:39:22,096
Aries just got back from the hospital.
Please, don't do this.

609
00:39:22,221 --> 00:39:24,432
Don't talk to my
mom like that, okay?

610
00:39:24,807 --> 00:39:25,975
Mom?

611
00:39:26,392 --> 00:39:28,769
Oh, so you've already
chosen another mom?

612
00:39:29,896 --> 00:39:31,689
You're really disrespectful, aren't you?

613
00:39:31,689 --> 00:39:33,691
You know, if I had
known you'd grow up like this,

614
00:39:33,691 --> 00:39:35,735
